From: GMS team <gms@example.com>
Subject: [PATCH] v1 BlockPool: expose evict-cached-block callback

Adds a public registration API on `BlockPool` so external KV connectors
can subscribe to "cached block has just been evicted" events. Today the
only signal is the private `_maybe_evict_cached_block` method, which
forces connectors (e.g. GMS's evict-to-host adapter) to monkey-patch
the class — fragile across minor vLLM releases.

The change:

  - Adds `BlockPool.register_evict_callback(callback)` where
    `callback` is `Callable[[KVCacheBlock, BlockHashWithGroupId], None]`.
  - `_maybe_evict_cached_block` invokes every registered callback right
    BEFORE the call returns True (i.e. before the block_hash mapping
    is dropped and before `block.reset_hash()`), so the callback can
    use `block.block_hash` to compute byte offsets.

This is purely additive; existing callers see no behavior change when
no callbacks are registered. Cost is one `if self._evict_callbacks:`
check per eviction, identical to the existing `self.metrics_collector`
gate already in this function.

Use case: external host-tier KV offload (engine evicts → connector
captures bytes to host RAM/NVMe before vLLM reuses the slot).

Signed-off-by: Maksim Khadkevich <mkhadkevich@nvidia.com>
Co-authored-by: Claude

---
 vllm/v1/core/block_pool.py | 28 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 28 insertions(+)

diff --git a/vllm/v1/core/block_pool.py b/vllm/v1/core/block_pool.py
index 0000000..0000000 100644
--- a/vllm/v1/core/block_pool.py
+++ b/vllm/v1/core/block_pool.py
@@ -1,7 +1,7 @@
 # SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0
 # SPDX-FileCopyrightText: Copyright contributors to the vLLM project
 from collections.abc import Iterable, Sequence
-from typing import Any
+from typing import Any, Callable

 from vllm.distributed.kv_events import (
     MEDIUM_GPU,
@@ -181,6 +181,29 @@ class BlockPool:

         self.metrics_collector = metrics_collector

+        # External evict-to-host hook: callbacks fire when a cached
+        # block is evicted (right before the block_hash mapping is
+        # cleared, so callbacks can still read `block.block_hash`).
+        # Use this from KVConnectors that mirror GPU KV to host RAM.
+        self._evict_callbacks: list[
+            Callable[[KVCacheBlock, BlockHashWithGroupId], None]
+        ] = []
+
+    def register_evict_callback(
+        self,
+        callback: Callable[[KVCacheBlock, BlockHashWithGroupId], None],
+    ) -> None:
+        """Register a callback fired on each prefix-cache eviction.
+
+        The callback receives `(block, block_hash_with_group_id)` and
+        is invoked synchronously inside `_maybe_evict_cached_block`,
+        before the block's hash is cleared. Throwing from the callback
+        will propagate out of the eviction path; connectors should
+        catch and log their own exceptions to avoid stalling the
+        scheduler.
+        """
+        self._evict_callbacks.append(callback)
+
     def get_cached_block(
         self, block_hash: BlockHash, kv_cache_group_ids: list[int]
     ) -> list[KVCacheBlock] | None:
@@ -371,6 +394,11 @@ class BlockPool:
             # eviction is not needed
             return False

+        # External evict-to-host hook: fire BEFORE reset_hash so
+        # callbacks can still read block.block_hash.
+        for cb in self._evict_callbacks:
+            cb(block, block_hash)
+
         block.reset_hash()

         if self.enable_kv_cache_events:
